              "question": "“Social stratification is universal but variable.” What does this statement mean?\n\u003cbr /\u003e",
              "order": "randomized",
              "presenterType": "RadioGroup",
              "presenterConfig": {
                "numberFormat": "none"
              },
              "choices": [
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_1",
                  "content": "The inequality of social stratification is found everywhere today, but the types and amounts of inequalities vary among societies."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_2",
                  "content": "A system of inequality not only gives some people more than others but also defines these arrangements as fair."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_3",
                  "content": "A meritocracy determines by birth who belongs in which level of social hierarchy."
                },
                {
                  "answerKey": "answer_4",
                  "content": "The rich create the social stratification that affects the rest of a given society."
